author: Jake Maxwell Watts
title: Singapore Stocks Rise With Region
text: [Dow Jones] Singapore’s FTSE Straits Times Index trades 1% higher at 3044.97 shortly after Friday’s open, following U.S. and Asian markets higher on a readjustment of expectations about interest rate rises in the U.S. Locally, there is a smattering of corporate news, and better-than-expected export data early Friday morning. Global Logistic Properties trades 1.3% higher after announcing a new property lease. Keppel DC REIT and CapitaLand Mall Trust are both flat, after the former announced dividends for the third quarter and the latter said it sold a Singapore mall property.
